      "end": 11.2,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.82,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.48,
      "end": 21.08,
      "text": "Asaps Fables, the Crow, and the Swan.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.38,
      "end": 28.1,
      "text": "A Crow was filled with envy on seeing the beautiful white plumage of a Swan, and thought",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.1,
      "end": 32.14,
      "text": "it was due to the water in which the Swan constantly bathed and swam.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.92,
      "end": 37.88,
      "text": "So he left the neighborhood of the altars, where he got his living by picking up bits",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 37.88,
      "end": 43.16,
      "text": "of the meat offered in sacrifice, and went and lived among the pools and streams.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 44.26,
      "end": 49.4,
      "text": "But though he bathed and washed his feathers many times a day, he didn't make them any",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 49.4,
      "end": 52.76,
      "text": "wider, and at last died of hunger in the bargain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 53.82,
      "end": 57.62,
      "text": "You may change your habits, but not your nature.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 58.64,
      "end": 61.46,
      "text": "End of the Crow and the Swan.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
